                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/5226a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers in Latin American
                            Countries</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In order that the Allied nations may not be embarrassed or interfered with in any
                    way in their prompt handling of all readjustments which changing conditions may
                    make necessary in the enemy trading or statutory lists, whether published or
                    confidential, you are instructed to advise any local association or associations
                    of Allied business houses to discontinue forthwith any black list published by
                    them or inspired by them, which is at variance with the official lists made
                    public by the Allied Governments under the direction of the properly constituted
                    boards. At the same time you will express to the associations of Allied business
                    houses which may be found within the district under your jurisdiction, the
                    appreciation of the War Trade Board for their active and effective cooperation
                    in preventing enemy houses from receiving American merchandise. Repeat to
                    consuls.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
